**************
The probability \(P(Y_7 < 27.3)\) is determined using the binomial distribution, where \(Y_7\) is the seventh order statistic of eight independent observations from a continuous distribution with the 70th percentile \(\pi_{0.7} = 27.3\). For a continuous distribution, \(P(X_i < 27.3) = 0.7\) for each observation.

The event \(Y_7 < 27.3\) is equivalent to at least seven observations being less than 27.3. Let \(N\) be the number of observations less than 27.3, so \(N \sim \text{Binomial}(n=8, p=0.7)\). Then:
\[
P(N \geq 7) = P(N=7) + P(N=8)
\]
\[
P(N=7) = \binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (0.3)^1 = 8 \times (0.7)^7 \times 0.3
\]
\[
P(N=8) = \binom{8}{8} (0.7)^8 (0.3)^0 = (0.7)^8
\]
Calculating the values:
\[
