Problem: 5.3-15. Three drugs are being tested for use as the treatment of a certain disease. Let $p_1, p_2$, and $p_3$ represent the probabilities of success for the respective drugs. As three patients come in, each is given one of the drugs in a random order. After $n=10$ "triples" and assuming independence, compute the probability that the maximum number of successes with one of the drugs exceeds eight if, in fact, $p_1=p_2=p_3=0.7$
 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The problem requires computing the probability that the maximum number of successes for one of the three drugs exceeds eight after 10 triples, with each drug having a success probability of 0.7 per administration.

Each drug is administered 10 times (once per triple), and the number of successes for each drug follows a binomial distribution: \( S_i \sim \text{Binomial}(10, 0.7) \) for \( i = 1, 2, 3 \). The random variables \( S_1, S_2, S_3 \) are independent.

The probability that the maximum number of successes exceeds eight is \( P(\max(S_1, S_2, S_3) > 8) \), which is equivalent to \( P(\max(S_1, S_2, S_3) \geq 9) \) since the number of successes is discrete.

This probability can be found using the complementary event:  
\[ P(\max(S_1, S_2, S_3) > 8) = 1 - P(\max(S_1, S_2, S_3) \leq 8) = 1 - P(S_1 \leq 8, S_2 \leq 8, S_3 \leq 8). \]

Due to independence:  
\[ P(S_1 \leq 8, S_2 \leq 8, S_3 \leq 8) = [P(S \leq 8)]^3, \]  
where \( S \sim \text{Binomial}(10, 0.7) \).

For \( S \sim \text{Binomial}(10, 0.7) \):  
\[ P(S > 8) = P(S = 9) + P(S = 10), \]  
\[ P(S = 10) = (0.7)^{10} = 0.0282475249, \]  
\[ P(S = 9) = \binom{10}{9} (0.7)^9 (0.3)^1 = 10 \times (0.7)^9 \times 0.3 = 10 \times 0.040353607 \times 0.3 = 0.121060821, \]  
\[ P(S > 8) = 0.121060821 + 0.0282475249 = 0.1493083459, \]  
\[ P(S \leq 8) = 1 - 0.1493083459 = 0.8506916541. \]

Then:  
\[ [P(S \leq 8)]^3 = (0.8506916541)^3. \]  
Calculating:  
\[ (0.8506916541)^2 = 0.723676289977481, \]  
\[ 0.723676289977481 \times 0.8506916541 = 0.615625372254845, \]  
\[ P(S_1 \leq 8, S_2 \leq 8, S_3 \leq 8) \approx 0.615625. \]

Finally:  
\[ P(\max(S_1, S_2, S_3) > 8) = 1 - 0.615625 = 0.384375. \]

Rounding to three significant figures (reasonable for probabilities), the result is 0.384.

