Problem: A doctor is concerned about the relationship between blood pressure and irregular heartbeats. Among her patients, she classifies blood pressures as high, normal, or low and heartbeats as regular or irregular and finds that 16\% have high blood pressure; (b) 19\% have low blood pressure; (c) $17 \%$ have an irregular heartbeat; (d) of those with an irregular heartbeat, $35 \%$ have high blood pressure; and (e) of those with normal blood pressure, $11 \%$ have an irregular heartbeat. What percentage of her patients have a regular heartbeat and low blood pressure? The unit of the answer should be % .
Solution: To determine the percentage of patients with a regular heartbeat and low blood pressure, the given information is used step by step. The blood pressure categories are high (H), normal (N), and low (L), and the heartbeat categories are regular (R) and irregular (I). The percentages provided are:

- 16% have high blood pressure (P(H) = 16%)
- 19% have low blood pressure (P(L) = 19%)
- 17% have an irregular heartbeat (P(I) = 17%)
- Of those with an irregular heartbeat, 35% have high blood pressure (P(H|I) = 35%)
- Of those with normal blood pressure, 11% have an irregular heartbeat (P(I|N) = 11%)

First, the percentage with normal blood pressure is calculated as:  
P(N) = 100% - P(H) - P(L) = 100% - 16% - 19% = 65%

Next, the joint probabilities involving irregular heartbeat are found:  
- P(H and I) = P(H|I) × P(I) = 35% × 17% = 0.35 × 0.17 = 0.0595, or 5.95%  
- P(I and N) = P(I|N) × P(N) = 11% × 65% = 0.11 × 0.65 = 0.0715, or 7.15%

The total with irregular heartbeat must equal the sum of those with irregular heartbeat in each blood pressure category:  
P(I) = P(I and H) + P(I and N) + P(I and L)  
17% = 5.95% + 7.15% + P(I and L)  
P(I and L) = 17% - 5.95% - 7.15% = 3.90%

The percentage with low blood pressure includes both irregular and regular heartbeat:  
P(L) = P(L and I) + P(L and R)  
19% = 3.90% + P(L and R)  
P(L and R) = 19% - 3.90% = 15.10%

Thus, the percentage with a regular heartbeat and low blood pressure is 15.10%. Rounding to three significant figures (as inputs like 17%, 35%, and 11% have two significant figures, but the result reasonably has three) gives 15.1%.

